Durban - A load of illegally dumped hazardous asbestos was discovered on Tuesday near the Treasure Beach environmental education centre on Marine Drive in the Bluff.

 In an attempt to “cut corners”, an ordinary hole was dug next to the asbestos to create a makeshift “landfill site” but this according to Desmond D'Sa from the South Durban Community Environmental Alliance(SDCEA), is not the proper procedure.
 “The proper procedure to dump asbestos is to get a licenced company who send people who wear waste suits and gloves. The asbestos is placed in bags and tied, then taken to a hazardous landfill site,” he said.

 







