 The asbestos was dumped in an area where community members walk and travel though.
 “If the dust from the asbestos gets into your system and into your blood it could block your arteries; and It’s directly linked to cancer,” he said.

 D'Sa added that the area also consists of an ecosystem with different species that could come into contact with the asbestos and be affected.
 The health department has been contacted and officials will be sent to the site on Wednesday.
